tart": 80.2, "end": 85.58, "text": " received and welcomed all the great and powerful Rishis"}, {"start": 85.58, "end": 87.86, "text": " who were assembled there"}, {"start": 89.22, "end": 92.82, "text": " and knew perfectly all the religious principles"}, {"start": 92.82, "end": 97.62, "text": " according to time and place"}, {"start": 97.62, "end": 102.18, "text": " Desha Kala Vibhagavit"}, {"start": 102.18, "end": 106.18, "text": " So the background for this verse is"}, {"start": 106.18, "end": 108.9, "text": " Bhishma is above the Buddhist body"}, {"start": 108.9, "end": 118.86, "text": " and the Pandavas have come to meet Bhishma Deva"}, {"start": 118.86, "end": 120.58, "text": " to receive instructions from him"}, {"start": 120.58, "end": 122.82, "text": " especially Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 122.82, "end": 126.1, "text": " and Krishna has also accompanied the Pandavas"}, {"start": 126.1, "end": 128.76, "text": " and all the great Rishis from all over the world"}, {"start": 128.76, "end": 130.5, "text": " all over the universe"}, {"start": 130.5, "end": 132.98, "text": " they have arrived there"}, {"start": 132.98, "end": 133.78, "text": " why?"}, {"start": 133.78, "end": 138.62, "text": " because a great soul is going to quit his body"}, {"start": 138.62, "end": 143.72, "text": " Bhishma Deva is one of the twelve Mahajanas"}, {"start": 143.72, "end": 148.66, "text": " so this quitting the body"}, {"start": 148.86, "end": 151.66000000000003, "text": " in the right consciousness"}, {"start": 151.66000000000003, "end": 155.98000000000002, "text": " is the perfection of one's life"}, {"start": 155.98000000000002, "end": 161.38000000000002, "text": " this is what Lord Krishna describes in the Bhagavad Gita"}, {"start": 161.38000000000002, "end": 167.18, "text": " Antakaale Chamam eva"}, {"start": 167.18, "end": 170.32000000000002, "text": " Smaran Muktva Kalevaram"}, {"start": 170.32000000000002, "end": 175.58, "text": " Yaprayati Samadbhavam Yati Nargajya Samushayaham"}, {"start": 175.58, "end": 177.5, "text": " Krishna says"}, {"start": 177.5, "end": 180.94, "text": " whoever quits his body remembering me alone"}, {"start": 180.94, "end": 184.06, "text": " attains to my nature"}, {"start": 184.06, "end": 187.98, "text": " and we will see in this chapter of Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 187.98, "end": 191.98, "text": " Bhishma Deva is going to quit his body"}, {"start": 192.14, "end": 194.38, "text": " thinking of Krishna"}, {"start": 194.38, "end": 197.26, "text": " glorifying Krishna"}, {"start": 197.26, "end": 201.82, "text": " and it is Bhishma's good fortune"}, {"start": 201.82, "end": 205.82, "text": " that Krishna is right in front of him"}, {"start": 207.5, "end": 210.62, "text": " but still"}, {"start": 210.62, "end": 213.1, "text": " Bhishma Deva received"}, {"start": 213.1, "end": 214.7, "text": " all the"}, {"start": 214.7, "end": 217.1, "text": " great sages who had come"}, {"start": 217.1, "end": 219.5, "text": " at that time"}, {"start": 219.5, "end": 224.86, "text": " so he received and welcomed all the great and powerful Rishis"}, {"start": 224.86, "end": 227.26, "text": " because he knew"}, {"start": 227.26, "end": 232.14, "text": " perfectly the religious principles according to time and place"}, {"start": 232.14, "end": 235.98, "text": " so Srila Prabhupada explains in the third part"}, {"start": 235.98, "end": 237.5, "text": " expert religionist"}, {"start": 237.5, "end": 239.98, "text": " know perfectly well"}, {"start": 239.98, "end": 243.26, "text": " how to adjust religious principles"}, {"start": 243.26, "end": 247.18, "text": " in terms of time and place"}, {"start": 249.58, "end": 254.22, "text": " according to time and place some adjustments have to be made"}, {"start": 254.22, "end": 258.06, "text": " the religious principles are given"}, {"start": 258.06, "end": 261.34, "text": " very elaborately in the dharma shastras"}, {"start": 261.34, "end": 266.62, "text": " but some adjustment has to be made 